                    <head>Laṭāʾif al-akhbār by Rashīd Khān</head>
                    <msContents
                        class="http://id.loc.gov/authorities/sh85001521 http://id.loc.gov/authorities/sh85064913">
                        <summary><title>Laṭāʾif al-akhbār</title>, called <title>Tārīkh-i
                                Qandahār</title> in the colophon, a detailed account of <persName
                                role="subject" key="viaf_27879596">Dārā Shukūh</persName>’s
                            unsuccessful siege of <name type="place" key="subject_n83042981"
                                >Qandahār</name> in 1063/1653 by Rashīd K̲h̲ān known as Muḥammad
                            Badīʻ, also called Rashīd Khān Badīʿ al-Zamān or Badīʿ al-Zamān
                            Mahābatkhānī. </summary>
